page.title: 10Sunday for Louise Holliday.
page.content: 04.30:My Dad gets up,has breakfast and goes to work (he milks cows). 08.30:Dad rings up from work to tell me to tell Mum to get up. 09.00:We get up (including Mum),get washed and get dressed (except Mum) into our best clothes. 09.30:Dad comes in and we have breakfast (except Mum). 09.45:I feed my rabbit while Mum and Dad get ready for church. 10.15:We go to our church,called Mount Zion,in Norwich. 10.45:We arrive at church. 12.45:We come out of church and go home. 13.15:We arrive home. 13.30:We eat our dinner (usually casserole in winter,salad in summer). 14.00:We finish dinner. 14.30:Dad goes back to work and the rest of the family watch T.V.
